ource":"reciIwO9bzHCw4Zqb","target":"recfrXyxhuYOczKTm","label":"mentions"},{"source":"reciIwO9bzHCw4Zqb","target":"recPkpwSKDIF9jQ3T","label":"mentions"},{"source":"reciIwO9bzHCw4Zqb","target":"recmCYBlOy0l5D1eB","label":"mentions"},{"source":"reciIwO9bzHCw4Zqb","target":"rec8hi9Ksp4awz9FJ","label":"mentions"},{"source":"reciIwO9bzHCw4Zqb","target":"recJ0N5yStBk9CjXA","label":"mentions"},{"source":"reciIwO9bzHCw4Zqb","target":"recc5WQixfPBowmwE","label":"mentions"}],"verses":[{"id":"rec3zyqPxwPBTgYtq","ref":"2Chr.9.1","text":"And when the queen of Sheba heard of the fame of Solomon, she came to prove Solomon with hard questions at Jerusalem, with a very great company, and camels that bare spices, and gold in abundance, and precious stones: and when she was come to Solomon, she communed with him of all that was in her heart."},{"id":"recJEYgghQh5ISx7a","ref":"2Chr.9.2","text":"And Solomon told her all her questions: and there was nothing hid from Solomon which he told her not."},{"id":"recdtHzKW1FeBuaRi","ref":"2Chr.9.3","text":"And when the queen of Sheba had seen the wisdom of Solomon, and the house that he had built,"},{"id":"recRJLQNWeq1FIeql","ref":"2Chr.9.4","text":"And the meat of his table, and the sitting of his servants, and the attendance of his ministers, and their apparel; his cupbearers also, and their apparel; and his ascent by which he went up into the house of the LORD; there was no more spirit in her."},{"id":"recXpou3b2xxavF4e","ref":"2Chr.9.5","text":"And she said to the king, It was a true report which I heard in mine own land of thine acts, and of thy wisdom:"},{"id":"recs4wdt2NzUbpJud","ref":"2Chr.9.6","text":"Howbeit I believed not their words, until I came, and mine eyes had seen it: and, behold, the one half of the greatness of thy wisdom was not told me: for thou exceedest the fame that I heard."},{"id":"recpfjqhHDbYrspcy","ref":"2Chr.9.7","text":"Happy are thy men, and happy are these thy servants, which stand continually before thee, and hear thy wisdom."},{"id":"recSWFAELI4e7J0wj","ref":"2Chr.9.8","text":"Blessed be the LORD thy God, which delighted in thee to set thee on his throne, to be king for the LORD thy God: because thy God loved Israel, to establish them for ever, therefore made he thee king over them, to do judgment and justice."}]}
